cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and relation extraction. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach for applying distant supervision to cross-sentence relation extraction. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves extracting information from biomedical research articles, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses machine learning techniques to extract relations.
